1. Download the filefetch repository.
2. Unzip it.
3. In the terminal run "chmod +x ./filefetch.sh" - makes the script executable.
4. Test commands:
- "./filefetch.sh test_data/" - displays directory's info
- "./filefetch.sh test_data/text.txt - displays text file's info
- "./filefetch.sh test_data/picture.png" - displays picture's info
- './filefetch.sh" - displays error
5. (Optional) Add to PATH for global use: 
- "sudo cp ./filefetch.sh /usr/local/bin"
